WEBVTT

00:02.135 --> 00:04.369
♪ Da, da, da-ba-da, da, da,
ba-da-ba-da-ba ♪

00:04.404 --> 00:05.871
♪ Da, da, da-ba-da, da, da ♪
Let's go!

00:05.906 --> 00:07.572
♪ We'll be there ♪

00:07.607 --> 00:10.242
♪ A wink and a smile
and a great old time ♪

00:10.277 --> 00:12.477
♪ Yeah, we'll be there ♪

00:12.512 --> 00:14.546
♪ Wherever we are,
there's some fun to be found ♪

00:14.581 --> 00:16.882
♪ We'll be there
when you turn that corner ♪

00:16.917 --> 00:18.216
♪ We'll jump out the bush ♪

00:18.251 --> 00:19.918
♪ With a big bear hug
and a smile ♪

00:19.953 --> 00:21.387
♪ We'll be there ♪

00:23.390 --> 00:27.659
♪♪

00:27.694 --> 00:28.860
[ Clock chiming ]

00:28.895 --> 00:31.229
Takeda:
Summer is ending.

00:31.264 --> 00:32.564
Don't leave me,
Saiyuri-chan.

00:32.599 --> 00:35.200
[ Train whistle blows ]
[ Both gasp ]

00:35.235 --> 00:37.035
Saiyuri:
I have to go, Takeda-Kun.

00:37.070 --> 00:39.438
♪♪

00:39.473 --> 00:42.574
This is a once-in-a-lifetime
opportunity for me.

00:42.609 --> 00:44.076
I have to go.

00:44.111 --> 00:45.577
But I've stopped at nothing
and overcome...

00:45.612 --> 00:47.879
Panda: "...and overcome
every obstacle between us.

00:47.914 --> 00:50.215
You're my one true love."

00:50.250 --> 00:54.086
[ Sighs ] Summer's
the best season for love.

00:54.121 --> 00:55.387
If only I could find someone

00:55.422 --> 00:59.224
that could make me
feel that way.

00:59.259 --> 01:01.259
Garçon,
another gluten-free

01:01.294 --> 01:03.562
chai-coconut milk
boba tea, please?

01:03.597 --> 01:05.730
[ Inhales sharply ]
Sorry, man.

01:05.765 --> 01:07.599
She got the last one.

01:07.634 --> 01:08.900
Huh?

01:08.935 --> 01:12.137
♪♪

01:15.742 --> 01:17.609
[ Thinking ]<i> Wow.</i>

01:20.147 --> 01:22.581
[ Slurping ]

01:22.616 --> 01:24.449
♪♪

01:24.484 --> 01:27.586
Panda:<i> Hello.</i>
<i>Forgive me for being so bold</i>

01:27.621 --> 01:29.087
<i>and confident.</i>

01:29.122 --> 01:32.591
<i>I couldn't help but notice</i>
<i>our love of drinks, literature,</i>

01:32.626 --> 01:35.160
<i>and handsome bears.</i>
[ Tink! ]

01:35.195 --> 01:39.064
<i>I think you are fascinating,</i>
<i>radiant, and really cool.</i>

01:39.099 --> 01:41.933
<i>And I want to know</i>
<i>more about you.</i>

01:41.968 --> 01:43.602
Okay, okay,
you can do this, okay.

01:43.637 --> 01:47.439
Just be calm, talk to her,
and remember to blink.

01:47.474 --> 01:49.107
Huh?

01:49.142 --> 01:52.244
No! No, no, no, no, no, no!

01:52.279 --> 01:54.579
She's gone! Just like that.

01:54.614 --> 01:57.949
My hopes, my dreams,
you've left me.

01:57.984 --> 02:00.485
Lost forever.

02:00.520 --> 02:04.623
What? Wha--
Her -- Her phone.

02:04.658 --> 02:06.124
<i>Huh? Panda case?</i>

02:06.159 --> 02:07.692
<i>Who is this girl?</i>

02:07.727 --> 02:09.528
<i>Wait a minute,</i>
<i>I have her phone.</i>

02:09.563 --> 02:13.465
<i>The most important thing</i>
<i>she owns is in my possession?!</i>

02:13.500 --> 02:15.200
It's a sign.

02:15.235 --> 02:16.501
Hey! Excuse me!

02:16.536 --> 02:18.436
Uh, that -- that girl
left her phone.

02:18.471 --> 02:20.805
Oh, shoot! I can take it
in case she comes back.

02:20.840 --> 02:22.440
Aah! Uh...
[ Laughs ]

02:22.475 --> 02:24.442
No, I-I can figure out
where she's heading

02:24.477 --> 02:26.945
and, um --
and return it to her.

02:26.980 --> 02:28.647
Hmm. Well, I may recall

02:28.682 --> 02:31.049
her mentioning
where she was headed.

02:31.084 --> 02:32.651
Really? What?
What did she say?

02:32.686 --> 02:35.687
Maybe I know.
- Maybe she said where she's --

02:35.722 --> 02:37.822
Bribe me.
[ Beep, beep, beep ]

02:37.857 --> 02:40.659
[ Ka-ching! ]
[ Grunting ]

02:40.694 --> 02:41.826
Okay, talk.

02:41.861 --> 02:44.162
[ Clears throat ]
- You didn't hear it from me.

02:44.197 --> 02:47.666
All I know is she said
something about a boat.

02:47.701 --> 02:50.168
[ Foghorn blows ]

02:50.203 --> 02:51.503
[ Pelican squawks ]

02:51.538 --> 02:53.038
[ Panting ]
[ Foghorn blows ]

02:53.073 --> 02:55.640
Huh? Oh, there it is!

02:55.675 --> 02:58.343
♪♪

02:58.378 --> 02:59.878
[ Gasps ]
It's her!

02:59.913 --> 03:02.013
A boat! I gotta find a boat!

03:02.048 --> 03:03.248
[ Pelican squawks ]

03:03.283 --> 03:04.549
Sir, sir,
I need a boat quick.

03:04.584 --> 03:06.318
I have to get on
that other ship.

03:06.353 --> 03:08.186
You want a boat
to catch another boat?

03:08.221 --> 03:11.156
Yes! Yes! My one true love
is on that boat.

03:11.191 --> 03:14.092
One true love?
- Ha! There's no such thing.

03:14.127 --> 03:16.194
No. Please, please!

03:16.229 --> 03:17.862
I need help.

03:17.897 --> 03:19.164
[ Captain clears throat ]

03:19.199 --> 03:23.068
Do me ears be hearing
ya need to set sail?

03:23.103 --> 03:25.837
Wait, huh?
Um, uh, are you serious?

03:25.872 --> 03:27.606
-I don't --
-You callin' me a joke?

03:27.641 --> 03:30.342
I come from generations
of sailors.

03:30.377 --> 03:32.077
I'll take you
to your lady.

03:32.112 --> 03:33.712
[ Spits ]

03:33.747 --> 03:36.748
Okay.
- And you can catch that ship?

03:36.783 --> 03:38.750
[ Cackles ]

03:38.785 --> 03:40.952
Aye.
We set sail at once.

03:40.987 --> 03:44.189
But be warned.
It'll cost ya.

03:44.224 --> 03:48.126
Uh, you like cola?

03:48.161 --> 03:51.529
[ Panting ]

03:51.564 --> 03:53.431
<i>I know the pain</i>
<i>of not having your phone,</i>

03:53.466 --> 03:54.799
<i>and I won't let that happen.</i>

03:54.834 --> 03:57.435
<i>I will find you,</i>
<i>no matter what.</i>

03:57.470 --> 03:59.404
It's worth it.
[ Panting ]

03:59.439 --> 04:01.206
It's worth it for love.

04:01.241 --> 04:02.607
I had a love, too.

04:02.642 --> 04:04.242
But he was
held back a grade.

04:04.277 --> 04:07.746
[ Foghorn blows ]
Huh?

04:07.781 --> 04:08.580
It's turning back.

04:08.615 --> 04:10.815
[ Cellphone beeping, buzzing ]

04:10.850 --> 04:13.118
Huh? A train.
She's leaving on a train.

04:13.153 --> 04:15.887
[ Pelican squawks ]
Wha--

04:15.922 --> 04:16.921
Um...

04:16.956 --> 04:18.957
[ Pelican squawks ]
Aah!

04:18.992 --> 04:20.992
No, no, no, no,
the phone!

04:21.027 --> 04:22.394
We have to go after it!

04:22.429 --> 04:24.596
[ Panting ]

04:29.002 --> 04:30.135
Stop!

04:30.170 --> 04:31.436
Why?
What's going on?

04:31.471 --> 04:34.239
-I can't go any further.
-What? Come on.

04:34.274 --> 04:36.841
That there
be Pelican Bay Island.

04:36.876 --> 04:42.747
Some say a madman lives there,
a lonely and terrifying man.

04:42.782 --> 04:45.283
Uh, could -- could you just
scoot a little closer?

04:45.318 --> 04:47.118
No.

04:47.153 --> 04:48.987
I mean, just a little?

04:49.022 --> 04:51.790
Okay.
[ Mumbles indistinctly ]

04:51.825 --> 04:53.958
[ Straining ]

04:53.993 --> 04:55.627
Whoa!

04:55.662 --> 04:58.163
[ Coughs ]
Thanks a lot.

04:58.198 --> 05:00.298
You've been warned!

05:00.333 --> 05:02.667
Weird kid.
[ Pelican squawks ]

05:02.702 --> 05:07.005
♪♪

05:07.040 --> 05:10.642
[ Gasps ]

05:10.677 --> 05:12.244
[ Coughs ]

05:14.414 --> 05:16.948
[ Grunts, sighs ]

05:16.983 --> 05:18.650
Aah! The phone!

05:18.685 --> 05:20.118
[ Grunts ]

05:20.153 --> 05:23.355
♪♪

05:25.859 --> 05:27.492
[ Cellphone ringing ]

05:27.527 --> 05:28.860
-[ Growls ]
-[ Laughs nervously ] Hey.

05:28.895 --> 05:31.029
No! No, stay away.
[ Pelican squawking ]

05:31.064 --> 05:32.797
Whoa! Aah!

05:32.832 --> 05:35.667
Huh?

05:35.702 --> 05:36.868
Whoa.
[ Pelican squawks ]

05:36.903 --> 05:38.403
Scientist:
Come on, Gary, quit it.

05:38.438 --> 05:40.338
It's not warm cookie time.

05:40.373 --> 05:44.175
[ Gasps ]
So, they sent another bear, huh?

05:44.210 --> 05:46.511
No. Oh, please, sir,
let -- let me explain.

05:46.546 --> 05:47.846
Don't play coy with me.

05:47.881 --> 05:49.681
You government bears
are all alike.

05:49.716 --> 05:52.317
Infiltrating my lab,
trying to steal my work.

05:52.352 --> 05:54.252
Well, not this time, bear.

05:54.287 --> 05:55.587
Wait.
No, you don't understand.

05:55.622 --> 05:57.722
The tables have turned.

05:57.757 --> 05:59.391
Take this!

06:01.694 --> 06:03.562
[ Grunting ]

06:06.032 --> 06:08.032
-Wha--
-Not so fast.

06:08.067 --> 06:09.401
[ Straining ]

06:09.436 --> 06:11.436
Please. Please, no,
you've got it all wrong.

06:11.471 --> 06:15.073
[ Clears throat ]
Using my new invention,

06:15.108 --> 06:16.674
powered by a lithium battery,

06:16.709 --> 06:21.746
this machine will transfer
our consciousness...

06:21.781 --> 06:23.615
-into each other's bodies.
-Aah! No!

06:23.650 --> 06:26.184
You don't want my body!
It -- It's round and squishy!

06:26.219 --> 06:29.287
By using their own government
spy bear against them,

06:29.322 --> 06:32.424
they'll never know!
[ Cackles ]

06:32.459 --> 06:35.226
[ Gary squawks ]
Ah, Gary.

06:35.261 --> 06:37.028
Perfect. A lithium battery.

06:37.063 --> 06:38.430
-No.
-At last,

06:38.465 --> 06:40.799
the final piece.

06:40.834 --> 06:43.968
Aah! What are you doing?!
That's not your phone!

06:44.003 --> 06:45.937
[ Laughs evilly ]

06:45.972 --> 06:48.873
♪♪

06:48.908 --> 06:50.375
[ Cackles ]

06:50.410 --> 06:52.377
Time to commence!

06:52.412 --> 06:53.578
Body swap!

06:53.613 --> 06:55.079
Aah!
What are you doing?!

06:55.114 --> 06:57.115
That's not your phone!

06:57.150 --> 06:58.583
I don't wanna swap.

06:58.618 --> 07:01.586
Wait a second.
I-I like my soft body.

07:01.621 --> 07:03.755
Aah! It's frying!
Wait, please stop!

07:03.790 --> 07:05.590
-I need that phone!
-[ Cackles ]

07:05.625 --> 07:07.759
I'll finally
have my revenge!

07:07.794 --> 07:11.596
No, please! I still have
so much to live for!

07:11.631 --> 07:13.932
I'll finally have the upper hand
over the government!

07:13.967 --> 07:16.568
I'll expose all their secrets
to the world.

07:16.603 --> 07:18.470
[ Cackles ]

07:18.505 --> 07:20.805
No! Please!
- I can't lose my body now.

07:20.840 --> 07:22.974
I need to meet her.
She's the one.

07:23.009 --> 07:24.309
[ Cackling ]

07:24.344 --> 07:26.478
I love her.
I just know it.

07:26.513 --> 07:29.247
She's my true love!

07:29.282 --> 07:30.281
Huh?

07:30.316 --> 07:33.685
[ Screaming ]

07:33.720 --> 07:35.053
What?

07:38.191 --> 07:40.291
True love.

07:40.326 --> 07:42.360
I had true love once.

07:42.395 --> 07:45.964
♪♪

07:45.999 --> 07:48.333
Um, what happened?

07:48.368 --> 07:50.802
[ Sighs ]
Amelia.

07:50.837 --> 07:54.272
She was the bright star
in my dark night sky.

07:54.307 --> 07:58.042
We met years ago during
what was my first internship.

07:58.077 --> 07:59.944
<i>Aah!</i>

07:59.979 --> 08:03.648
And right then,
I knew she was the one.

08:03.683 --> 08:06.284
We worked together,
blundered together,

08:06.319 --> 08:08.219
made discoveries together.

08:08.254 --> 08:10.355
Amelia was the one.

08:10.390 --> 08:11.823
But they took her away!

08:11.858 --> 08:15.493
She was offered a job in space!

08:15.528 --> 08:16.895
She was gone.

08:16.930 --> 08:20.665
I couldn't sleep.
I roamed the streets for weeks.

08:20.700 --> 08:23.234
I was eating stuff off
the ground, fighting with birds.

08:23.269 --> 08:25.837
Gary was the only one
who didn't shun me.

08:25.872 --> 08:28.172
I was too absorbed in my work.

08:28.207 --> 08:31.409
I missed my chance
to tell her how I felt.

08:31.444 --> 08:32.877
Now she's gone.

08:32.912 --> 08:34.846
Man, I'm -- I'm sorry
to hear that, dude.

08:34.881 --> 08:36.915
Don't make the same mistake
I did, bear!

08:36.950 --> 08:38.983
Don't live
with a regret like mine.

08:39.018 --> 08:40.685
[ Beep ]

08:40.720 --> 08:42.687
[ Gasps ]
The phone!

08:44.924 --> 08:46.024
Ah! Oh, my gosh.

08:46.059 --> 08:47.926
The phone is okay.
Thank goodness.

08:47.961 --> 08:50.495
[ Cellphone beeping, buzzing ]
[ Gasps ]

08:50.530 --> 08:52.597
Well, Gary,
let's go have some cookies.

08:52.632 --> 08:54.532
Oh, no, no, no, no.
It's already 5:30.

08:54.567 --> 08:56.668
I'm not gonna make it
off this island in time.

08:56.703 --> 08:59.370
I've got just the thing.
You got the keys, Gary?

08:59.405 --> 09:00.872
[ Gary squawks ]

09:00.907 --> 09:03.909
♪♪

09:05.712 --> 09:07.412
Her train leaves at 6:00!

09:07.447 --> 09:08.980
We'll make it!

09:10.817 --> 09:12.884
Do it for me and Amelia!

09:12.919 --> 09:14.085
[ Gary squawks ]

09:14.120 --> 09:16.287
[ Panting ]

09:16.322 --> 09:17.656
Wha--

09:19.959 --> 09:23.361
[ Panting ]

09:23.396 --> 09:25.630
Oh.

09:25.665 --> 09:27.398
[ Cellphone beeps, buzzes ]

09:27.433 --> 09:30.468
-[ Sighs ]
-Excuse me.

09:30.503 --> 09:32.804
Uh, is that my phone?

09:32.839 --> 09:34.572
[ Gasps ]
- Panda: [ Thinking ]<i> It's her.</i>

09:34.607 --> 09:36.574
<i>It's finally her.</i>

09:36.609 --> 09:39.077
Oh, yes, it is yours.
I-I found it at a boba shop.

09:39.112 --> 09:41.412
I've been trying
to get it back to you.

09:41.447 --> 09:43.748
Really? Wow.
I don't know what to say.

09:43.783 --> 09:45.583
I-I mean, thanks.

09:45.618 --> 09:47.785
Oh, sure.
'Twas nothing.

09:47.820 --> 09:49.821
<i>I am being so cool right now.</i>

09:49.856 --> 09:51.923
I hope it wasn't too much
trouble finding me?

09:51.958 --> 09:54.592
Oh, uh, it was -- it was no
trouble at all.

09:54.627 --> 09:57.061
You know, I-I was in the area,
m-more or less.

09:57.096 --> 09:59.430
Oh, by the way,
I'm -- I'm Panda.

09:59.465 --> 10:00.765
I'm Amanda.

10:00.800 --> 10:03.267
[ Laughs ]
- Oh, our names sound alike.

10:03.302 --> 10:04.836
Oh. [ Chuckles ]
Yeah.

10:04.871 --> 10:07.271
<i>Okay, Panda,</i>
<i>this is your chance.</i>

10:07.306 --> 10:08.973
Uh, so, Amanda, um...

10:09.008 --> 10:12.944
Man:<i> Express train for the Bay</i>
<i>Area Airport leaving now.</i>

10:12.979 --> 10:14.812
That's my train.
I'm late for a flight.

10:14.847 --> 10:17.281
I'm -- I'm moving
out of the Bay Area.

10:17.316 --> 10:22.420
But thank you so much again.

10:22.455 --> 10:24.689
Hey, Panda?

10:24.724 --> 10:26.257
If I ever
lose my phone again,

10:26.292 --> 10:28.593
I hope you're the one
that finds it.

10:28.628 --> 10:30.495
♪♪

10:30.530 --> 10:33.931
♪ We surround ♪

10:33.966 --> 10:38.102
♪ With a gentle beat that ♪

10:38.137 --> 10:39.937
Takeda:
She had her own journey to take.

10:39.972 --> 10:42.507
And while our overlapping paths
ended here,

10:42.542 --> 10:46.544
I was met with a bigger world,
climbed and crossed continents,

10:46.579 --> 10:49.013
and fought foes
in the name of love.

10:49.048 --> 10:51.315
In the end,
these were all experiences

10:51.350 --> 10:55.720
which would ready me for the
next time summer comes along.

10:55.755 --> 10:59.190
Well, until next summer.

10:59.225 --> 11:00.658
[ Gary squawks ]

11:00.693 --> 11:03.161
Um, another boba tea, please?

11:04.664 --> 11:07.666
♪♪
